#. type: Title ###
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/cryptonight.md:73
#, no-wrap
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/cryptonight.md:76
msgid ""
"CryptoNight attempts to make memory access a bottleneck for performance "
"(\"memory hardness\"). It has three steps:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/cryptonight.md:80
msgid ""
"Initialize large area of memory with pseudo-random data. This memory is "
"known as the scratchpad."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2. '
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/cryptonight.md:80
msgid ""
"Perform numerous read/write operations at pseudo-random (but deterministic) "
"addresses on the scratchpad."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '3. '
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/cryptonight.md:80
msgid "Hash the entire scratchpad to produce the resulting value."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/cryptonight.md:81
#, no-wrap
msgid "Step 1: scratchpad initialization"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/cryptonight.md:84
msgid ""
"Firstly, the input data is hashed with Keccak-1600. This results in 200 "
"bytes of pseudorandom data (1600 bits == 200 bytes)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/cryptonight.md:87
msgid ""
"These 200 bytes become a seed to generate a larger, 2MB-wide buffer of "
"pseudorandom data, by applying AES-256 encryption."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/cryptonight.md:89
msgid "The first 0..31 bytes of Keccak-1600 hash are used as AES key."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/cryptonight.md:93
msgid ""
"The encryption is performed on 128 bytes-long payloads until 2MB is ready.  "
"The first payload are Keccak-1600 bytes 66..191.  The next payload is "
"encryption result of the previous payload."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/cryptonight.md:95
msgid "Each 128-byte payload is actually encrypted 10 times."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/cryptonight.md:96
#, no-wrap
msgid "The details are a bit more nuanced, see \"Scratchpad Initialization\" in [CryptoNote Standard](https://cryptonote.org/cns/cns008.txt).  \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/cryptonight.md:98
#, no-wrap
msgid "Step 2: memory-hard loop"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/cryptonight.md:101
msgid ""
"The second step is basically 524288 iterations of a simple stateful "
"algorithm."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/cryptonight.md:104
msgid ""
"Each algorithm iteration reads from and writes back to the scratchpad, at "
"pseudorandom-but-deterministic locations."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/cryptonight.md:107
msgid ""
"Critically, next iteration depends on the state prepared by previous "
"iterations.  It is not possible to directly calculate state of future "
"iterations."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/cryptonight.md:109
msgid ""
"The specific operations include AES, XOR, 8byte_mul, 8byte_add - operations "
"that are CPU-friendly (highly optimized on modern CPU-s)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/cryptonight.md:111
msgid ""
"The goal here is to make memory latency the bottleneck in attempt to close "
"the gap between potential ASIC-s and general purpose CPU-s."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/cryptonight.md:112
#, no-wrap
msgid "Step 3: hashing"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/cryptonight.md:115
msgid "The final step (simplifying) is to:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/cryptonight.md:123
msgid "combine original Keccak-1600 output with the whole scratchpad"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/cryptonight.md:123
msgid "pick the hashing algorithm based on 2 low-order bits of the result"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '    * '
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/cryptonight.md:123
msgid "0=BLAKE-256"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '    * '
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/cryptonight.md:123
msgid "1=Groestl-256"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '    * '
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/cryptonight.md:123
msgid "2=JH-256"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '    * '
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/cryptonight.md:123
msgid "3=Skein-256"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/cryptonight.md:123
msgid "hash the result with selected function"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/proof-of-work/cryptonight.md:125
msgid ""
"The resulting 256-bit hash is the final output of CryptoNight algorithm."
msgstr ""

